<br>
You want a high level toon with some gear and a reputation and all that without dealing with the low level drudgery? Ebay till you can’t ebay no more.<br>
<br>
You want phat lewts and plat with minimal effort? Ebay, baby, ebay.<br>
<br>
You want to prove you have phat class skills that you learned with your 60+ toon on alternate_server_01 and feel that levelling a new character is a waste of your time? 4 letters - ybea, figure it out.<br>
<br>
You want the fastrack easiest path? I’m sure by now you have it figured out.<br>
<br>
You want to play the game and earn the respect of a goodly sized chunk of this server? Eb.... oh no wait, thats gonna cost you something other than cash. Effort, I believe, is the only currency that can buy that.<br>
<br>
Now to be fair, I suppose after the toon is bought alot of effort could raise that char’s rep a bit, but don’t ever expect those that knew the “real” so-and-so to ever fully accept the “evil-ebay-cloned-so-and-so.” And further more, expect every dollar you spend on ebay loot and plat to drop some folks opinions of you a notch or two. On the positive side, there is a growing number of folks that won’t care, but that’s largely because folks don’t like pointing at mirrors.<br>
<br>
And as far as arguing about this goes?<br>
<br>
Do you ebayers really think the anti-ebay horde (AEH), myself included, is going to have a change of heart? If so, allow me to strip you of your innocence. No. We want you beaten with wiffle ball bats until you pee yourselves and promise to never do it again.<br>
<br>
Are any one of you going to have an epiphany and delete all your toons and lewt bought with RL green? Of course not and any one of the AEH that is holding his or her breath waiting for that to happen might want to find a nice soft spot to land so when s/he passes out, it won’t hurt too much. You may pelt us with wiffle balls until we awake if said scenario occurs.<br>
<br>
So lets just get together, play some wiffle ball (Team Ebay versus the AEH winning team gets lifetime supply of absolutely nothing) and put this topic to rest as this argument is really going nowhere, and will only continue to do so. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/JCOLE1/pnimages/talastiusportraitsig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=465503"> What are you looking at?!? </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=decius1@firionavie>Decius1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/2/03 6:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ebay Guilds (the post that will give you fuckers a clue)</span><hr size=1> It's sort of like ticket touts.<br>
<br>
Ticket touts are great if you really wanted to see that concert but it was sold out. You shell out a fortune, voluntarily, and get your ticket. Everybody's happy.<br>
<br>
Until you realise that the reason the concert was sold out was because half the tickets were bought by touts.<br>
<br>
[this is a very loose metaphor, but:<br>
<br>
1) Ebayed gear diminishes the success of those who have worked for their stuff. <br>
2) Ebayed characters take up spaces in guilds, which others may have been aiming for but no one can level faster than the ebay team. <br>
3) People who have no qualms about making RL money from ebaying probably have no qualms about, say, buying all the high end gear / tradeskill components in the bazaar, thus giving themselves a monopoly, then doubling their prices. <br>
4) Ebayed people are often very skilled, yet ebaying increases anonymity, and it is only through lack of anonymity that we are able to &quot;police&quot; our server i.e. person X is a griefer... or did they ebay? Or did they just pretend to ebay in order to clear their rep?<br>
5+) &amp;c there are probably a billion and one other little reasons which I didn't think of on the spur of the moment<br>
<br>
In short, ebay used responsibly by nice people is fine. But unfortunately it is also used by some rather more unsavoury types who use it for their own, exploitative ends.]<br>
<br>
Shackleton<br>
