<br>
There is a reason it's in the same breath as the anything that sucks too much bandwith clause. It's there to give the recourse if somebody comes along and tries to make a buisness out of it. Too many folks doing this and it just sucks resources away from 'real' customers. So they have to discourage it to some degree. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~mcjohnson/images/EQ/sig52.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
